<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="597" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,310,152,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The ZSI collection has one glass tube of this species, which is labeled as ‘holotype’ (3827/18), containing a female specimen in fairly good condition, with broken legs and intact genitalia. Judging from the original illustration of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R.Wight" authorityYear="1848" box="[224,331,223,247]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">epigynum</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Crews &amp; Harvey, 2011" authorityName="Crews &amp; Harvey" authorityYear="2011" box="[371,805,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Selenopidae" genus="Makdiops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shiva">
<emphasis box="[371,541,223,247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Makdiops shiva</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Crews, S. C. &amp; Harvey, M. S." box="[551,805,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref2596" refString="Crews, S. C. &amp; Harvey, M. S. (2011) The spider family Selenopidae (Arachnida, Araneae) in Australasia and the Oriental region. ZooKeys, 99, 1 - 103. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 99.723" type="journal article" year="2011">Crews &amp; Harvey, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, this species may be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tikader" baseAuthorityYear="1969" box="[1272,1436,223,247]" class="Arachnida" family="Selenopidae" genus="Makdiops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agumbensis">
<emphasis box="[1272,1436,223,247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">M. agumbensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation box="[259,339,259,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,737,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-247@1.[151,1435,729,1909]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1A–D. Makdiops agumbensis (Tikader, 1969) (Holotype female NZC-ZSI-3827/18). A Habitus, dorsal. B Prosoma, dorsal. C Epigynum, ventral. D Type label. Scale bars:A–B, 2 mm; C, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4387581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4387581/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
with 
<bibRefCitation author="Crews, S. C. &amp; Harvey, M. S." box="[402,647,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref2596" refString="Crews, S. C. &amp; Harvey, M. S. (2011) The spider family Selenopidae (Arachnida, Araneae) in Australasia and the Oriental region. ZooKeys, 99, 1 - 103. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 99.723" type="journal article" year="2011">Crews &amp; Harvey 2011</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 89). However, confirmation requires the examination of the vulva of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tikader" baseAuthorityYear="1969" box="[151,313,295,319]" class="Arachnida" family="Selenopidae" genus="Makdiops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agumbensis">
<emphasis box="[151,313,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">M. agumbensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for which we did not get dissection permission.
</paragraph>
